12 "§ 74D-3. Exemptions.
13 The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to:to the following:
14 (1) A person, firm, association or corporation that sells or manufactures alarm
15 security systems, unless the person, firm, association or corporation makes
16 personal solicitations at a residence or business to advise, design, or consult
17 on specific types and specific locations of alarm security system devices,
18 installs, services, monitors, or responds to alarm security systems at or from a
19 protected premises or a premises to be protected and thereby obtains
20 knowledge of specific application or location of the alarm security system. A
21 person licensed under this Chapter may hire a consultant to troubleshoot a
22 location or installation for a period of time not to exceed 48 hours in a
23 one-month period if the licensee submits a report to the Board within 30 days
24 from the date of the consultation designating the consultant as a temporary
25 consultant;
26 (2) Installation, servicing or responding to fire alarm systems or any alarm device
27 which is installed in a motor vehicle, aircraft or boat;boat.
28 (3) Installation or service of an alarm electronic security system on property
29 owned by or leased to the installer;installer.
30 (4) An alarm monitoring company located in another state which demonstrates to
31 the Board's satisfaction that it does not conduct any business through a
32 personal representative present in this State but which solicits and conducts
33 business solely through interstate communication facilities such as telephone
34 messages, earth satellite relay stations and the United States postal service;
35 and
36 (5) A person or business providing alarm systems services to a State agency or
37 local government if that person or business has been providing those services
38 to the State agency or local government for more than five years prior to the
39 effective date of this Chapter, and the State agency or local government joins
40 with the person or business in requesting the application of this exemption.
41 (6) Installation or service of a locking device that records entry and exit data and
42 does not transmit the data in real time to an on-site or off-site monitoring
43 location, provided the installer is licensed by the North Carolina Locksmith
44 Licensing Board.
45 (7) An entity through which a customer accesses marketing or advertising
46 material or installation instructions for a security system.
47 (b) A person licensed under this Chapter may utilize a consultant or manufacturer's
48 representative to troubleshoot a location or installation if accompanied by the licensee and the
49 licensee submits a report to the Board within 30 days from the date of the consultation designating
50 the consultant as a temporary consultant.
