1 (a) The Alarm Security Systems Licensing Board is hereby established.
2 (b) The Board shall consist of seven members: the Secretary of Public Safety or his or
3 her designee; two persons appointed by the Governor, one of whom shall be licensed under this
4 Chapter and one of whom shall be a public member; two persons appointed by the General
5 Assembly upon the recommendation of the President Pro Tempore of the Senate in accordance
6 with G.S. 120-121, one of whom shall be licensed under this Chapter and one of whom shall be
7 a public member; and two persons appointed by the General Assembly upon the recommendation
8 of the Speaker of the House of Representatives in accordance with G.S. 120-121, one of whom
9 shall be licensed under this Chapter and one of whom shall be a public member.
10 (c) Each member shall be appointed for a term of three years and shall serve until a
11 successor is installed. No With the exception of the Secretary or his or her designee, no member
12 shall serve more than two complete three-year consecutive terms. The term of each member,
13 other than the Attorney General or his designee, who is serving on August 7, 1989, shall terminate
14 on June 30, 1989. Of the appointments made by the General Assembly upon the recommendation
15 of the President of the Senate to begin on July 1, 1989, one member shall be for a term of one
16 year and one member shall be for a term of three years. Of the appointments made by the General
17 Assembly upon the recommendation of the Speaker of the House of Representatives, one member
18 shall be appointed for a term of two years and one member shall be appointed for a term of three
19 years. Thereafter all terms shall be for three years.
